+    138:     def calculate_semantic_properties(self, emoji: str, multivector: Dict[str, Any], 
+    139:                                     count: int, contexts: List[str]) -> Dict[str, Any]:
+    140:         """Calculate semantic properties for the emoji"""
+    141:         
+    142:         # Calculate complexity based on multivector norm and count
+    143:         complexity = float(multivector["norm"] * np.log(count + 1))
+    144:         
+    145:         # Calculate frequency score (normalized)
+    146:         frequency_score = min(1.0, count / 10000.0)  # Normalize to max 10k occurrences
+    147:         
+    148:         # Calculate context diversity
+    149:         unique_contexts = len(set(contexts[:100]))  # Limit to first 100 contexts
+    150:         context_diversity = min(1.0, unique_contexts / 50.0)  # Normalize to max 50 unique contexts
+    151:         
+    152:         # Calculate universe system relevance
+    153:         is_universe_emoji = emoji in self.universe_emojis
+    154:         universe_relevance = 1.0 if is_universe_emoji else 0.0
+    155:         
+    156:         # Calculate semantic distance to universe center
+    157:         if is_universe_emoji:
+    158:             universe_center = np.mean([self.generate_clifford_multivector(ue)["coefficients"] 
+    159:                                      for ue in self.universe_emojis], axis=0)
+    160:             semantic_distance = float(np.linalg.norm(
+    161:                 np.array(multivector["coefficients"]) - universe_center
+    162:             ))
+    163:         else:
+    164:             semantic_distance = 1.0  # Max distance for non-universe emojis
+    165:         
+    166:         return {
+    167:             "complexity": complexity,
+    168:             "frequency_score": frequency_score,
+    169:             "context_diversity": context_diversity,
+    170:             "universe_relevance": universe_relevance,
+    171:             "semantic_distance": semantic_distance,
+    172:             "is_universe_emoji": is_universe_emoji

+     45:    ```rust
+     46:    pub fn generate_multivector_from_string(input: &str) -> SolMultivector {
+     47:        let mut hasher = Sha256::new();
+     48:        hasher.update(input.as_bytes());
+     49:        let result = hasher.finalize();
+     50:        
+     51:        let mut coeffs = [0.0f32; 8];
+     52:        for i in 0..8 {
+     53:            coeffs[i] = (result[i] as f32 / 255.0) * 2.0 - 1.0;
+     54:        }
+     55:        SolMultivector::from_vector(coeffs.to_vec()).unwrap()
+     56:    }
+     57:    ```

+    146:     fn calculate_quality_score(&self, entries: &[LogEntry]) -> f64 {

+    166:                 total_indicators += 1;

+    168:

+    170:             if line.contains("```") || line.contains("cargo run") || line.contains("git commit") {
+    171:                 score += 2.0;
+    172:                 total_indicators += 1;

+    174:             
+    175:             // Error indicators (-1 point)
+    176:             if line.contains("error:") || line.contains("failed") || line.contains("Error") {

+    287:     pub fn paginate(&self, page: usize) -> Page<LogEntry> {
+    288:         let total_entries = self.timestamp_ordering.len();
+    289:         let total_pages = (total_entries + self.page_size - 1) / self.page_size;
+    290:         
+    291:         let start_idx = page.saturating_sub(1) * self.page_size;
+    292:         let end_idx = std::cmp::min(start_idx + self.page_size, total_entries);
+    293:         
+    294:         let items: Vec<LogEntry> = self.timestamp_ordering
+    295:             .values()
+    296:             .skip(start_idx)
+    297:             .take(self.page_size)
+    298:             .cloned()
+    299:             .collect();
+    300:         
+    301:         let (start_time, end_time) = if !items.is_empty() {
+    302:             (items.first().unwrap().timestamp, items.last().unwrap().timestamp)
+    303:         } else {
+    304:             (Utc::now(), Utc::now())
+    305:         };
+    306:         
+    307:         let navigation = PageNavigation {
+    308:             previous_timestamp: if page > 1 { 
+    309:                 self.timestamp_ordering.values().nth(start_idx.saturating_sub(1)).map(|e| e.timestamp)
+    310:             } else { 
+    311:                 None 
+    312:             },
+    313:             next_timestamp: if end_idx < total_entries {
+    314:                 self.timestamp_ordering.values().nth(end_idx).map(|e| e.timestamp)
+    315:             } else {
+    316:                 None
+    317:             },
+    318:             can_continue: end_idx < total_entries,
+    319:             can_go_back: page > 1,
+    320:             bookmark_id: None,
+    321:         };
+    322:         
+    323:         let metadata = PageMetadata {
+    324:             total_concepts: 0, // Will be filled by knowledge extraction
+    325:             emoji_density: 0.0,
+    326:             quality_score: 0.0,
+    327:             reaction_count: 0,
+    328:             hot_take_count: 0,
+    329:         };
+    330:         
+    331:         Page {
+    332:             page_number: page,
+    333:             total_pages,
+    334:             items,
+    335:             timestamp_range: (start_time, end_time),
+    336:             navigation,
+    337:             metadata,
+    338:         }
+    339:     }
